latestPosts.caption:
one year since i lost you, one year since my world crumbled. I don’t think I have accepted that you are no longer here, I just assume you are still here somewhere but not talking to me. I remember the two months you were in hospital, I remember the twelve days, but after that? I was alone, we were alone with no one to comfort us, to teach us how to deal with grief. I still can’t breathe, by each passing day I become more lost, more anxious with the thought that I have limited photos and now an entire lifetime of your birthday’s and death anniversary’s. I remember seeing that cloud on 28th May at 5:30pm, you were gone by then but I didn’t know, that cloud gave me the indication. I regret not telling you each day that I am proud of you, that one day maybe, if I can become even 1% like you, I would be blessed. 
whatever I achieve, wherever I go, whomever I meet, it’s not worth it, not without you.
Why was it me who had to lose you and live with it? Why was it you who had to go away? we will never know.
Cutaa you were the best human to walk this earth and you are missed.
Everytime someone talks sports or politics or even of the gst paper I gave yesterday, I miss you, I miss you because I think we were a team always discussing things, waking up at 3:30am to watch games, you locking me in a room because you thought that is how your favourite team wins, engaging in family debates at 9pm with KBC, I will always be in awe of the man you were, you just left without telling me how it would be doing it all alone, but I guess that is my punishment for leaving you alone too. You were so mature but you always did one thing to let us know that you are a kid, and that is someone I will always try to be.
It would have been an amazing year anshi, you turning 18, me turning 21, mumma papa’s 30th and didi turning 25, we would have celebrated but yet here we were with shaking hands and shortness of breath on those days. 
I miss you, I love you and I can’t believe one year has passed because it feels like everything just happened yesterday, anyways I hope you are okay wherever you are and I just know you are at peace and I see the white bird, I see it everytime I need to❤️‍🩹

latestPosts.caption:
you were a dream LSR, my dream, and you are a dream that is fulfilled now. I came to you as a scared young girl and you made sure I leave as a confident independent woman. 
The women I met here were the most supporting and uplifting set who always cared for others, who knew how to be pillars when time was challenging them. 
These red walls were my first home away from home, not only did they shape me but also gave me a path, a way to follow after college, taking them with me. You gave me lessons, you gave me cheers and most importantly you gave me strength LSR, strength to never give up, strength to bounce back when my world came crumbling down, I don’t know what I would have done without you. 
But this post, is for all of you, for all my ELSAs. Thank you for being my magic✨
